On Sun, 28 Mar 1999, Chris Wedgwood wrote:
> I'm surprised someone hasn't argues to hack the kernel to provide
> certain bultins (shudder)...
Did it. I wrote a romdisk driver for 2.0.x that lets you use a read only
filesystem image that can be in arbitrary regions of memory, including
embedded in the kernel image. Not quite running in kernel space, but still
"builtin".
